@startuml retry_dlq_pattern

title BTG Desafio - Padrão Retry / Dead Letter Queue (Recomendado)

note as disclaimer
    Este diagrama descreve o padrão recomendado para
    resiliência no consumo de mensagens.
    A implementação atual usa QueueBuilder.durable() sem DLQ.
    Recomenda-se adicionar DLQ para produção.
end note

rectangle "RabbitMQ" {
    queue "order.queue.created\n[durable]" as main_q
    queue "order.queue.created.retry\n[durable, x-message-ttl=5000ms]" as retry_q
    queue "order.queue.created.dlq\n[durable]" as dlq
    component "order.exchange" as exchange
    component "order.exchange.retry" as retry_exchange
    component "order.exchange.dlq" as dlq_exchange
}

component "ms-order\n@RabbitListener" as consumer
component "DLQ Monitor\n(alerta / reprocessamento manual)" as dlq_monitor

exchange --> main_q : routing key: order.created
main_q --> consumer : entrega (tentativa 1)

consumer --> retry_exchange : falha\n(x-death count < 3)
retry_exchange --> retry_q : aguarda TTL (5s)
retry_q --> main_q : reencaminha para fila principal

consumer --> dlq_exchange : 3 tentativas falharam
dlq_exchange --> dlq : mensagem na DLQ
dlq --> dlq_monitor : monitoramento e alerta

note right of consumer
    Estratégia de retry:
    tentativa 1: imediato
    tentativa 2: após 5s (via retry queue)
    tentativa 3: após mais 5s
    → DLQ após 3 falhas
end note

note right of dlq
    Dead Letter Queue permite
    auditoria e reprocessamento
    manual das mensagens que
    falharam persistentemente.
end note

@enduml